    <item>
      <title>Codegen Update Expected</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-25-codegen-update-expected/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Mar 2025 07:25:05 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-25-codegen-update-expected/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Expect an update to &lt;a href=&#34;https://crates.io/crates/xenon-codegen&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer nofollow&#34;&gt;xenon-codegen&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; around 3:05 to 3:30 EST today. I would push it earlier but cargo publish doesn&amp;rsquo;t work on my school&amp;rsquo;s WiFi. After &lt;a href=&#34;https://crates.io/crates/xenon-codegen&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer nofollow&#34;&gt;xenon-codegen&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; is finished, I will start implimenting the parser. Then, I will probably work on XVM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>XVM Postponed</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-25-xvm-postponed/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Mar 2025 06:55:27 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-25-xvm-postponed/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I have postponed development on XVM whilst I work on porting the new Xenon syntax to &lt;a href=&#34;https://crates.io/crates/xenon-codegen&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer nofollow&#34;&gt;xenon-codegen&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Handle Compiler?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-how-to-handle-compiler/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2025 14:57:24 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-how-to-handle-compiler/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m still debating, but for now I think the compiler for Xenon will work using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://llvm.org/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer nofollow&#34;&gt;LLVM&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; IR. I don&amp;rsquo;t think I want to write my own compiler for each target, and having a unified platform other languages use helps in bug fixes. Also, sorry for lack of updates over the weekend. I was working on another project.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Syntax Update</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-syntax-update/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2025 13:01:55 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-syntax-update/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The syntax for Xenon has been &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/docs/syntax.md&#34; &gt;rewritten in Antlr4&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; with some new features. An update to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://crates.io/crates/xenon-codegen&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer nofollow&#34;&gt;xenon-codegen&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; crate will soon follow. I expect to finish the updated parser by 4/30, but hopefully earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>XVM</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-xvm/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2025 07:34:14 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/updates/2025/03-24-xvm/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I have begun work on a code generation backend called XVM.&#xA;The IR is basically assembly, but it compiles platform independently.&#xA;XVM will be avalible on crates.io soon.&#xA;Sorry for the delays on new stuff for Xenon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
